![](data:image/png;base64,) Doxee Platform **Dashboards **allow to monitor the most relevant metrics, depending on your configuration.

- The **Favorite **section lists the dashboards that you have marked as favorites.

- The **Dashboards **section lists all available dashboards, based on your access permissions.

> Tip

To access the **Home &gt; Dashboards **view, click the **ALL DASHBOARDS **button in the Dashboards widget on the [Home page](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-home-documentation).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

#### Marking a dashboard as favorite
- Move your mouse over the name of the required dashboard.

- Click the  ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon displayed on the right to add it to your favorite dashboards.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

You may favorite as many dashboards as you like, but the Home page **Dashboards **widget only displays the last 4 dashboards added to your favorites.

## Accessing a dashboard
- Move your mouse over the name of the required dashboard.

- Click on the **Open **link displayed on the right to open the selected dashboard in a new browser tab.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click on the **Dashboards **link on the breadcrumb bar at the top to go back to the **Dashboards **view; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,) Click on the **Home **link to go back to the Doxee Platform Home page; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Zooming in on data
To view detailed data on a particular point in the chart, move your mouse pointer over the desired point, as shown in the example below. 

To enlarge a specific section of the chart and zoom in on data, select the desired rectangular area using your mouse.

> Tip

To return to the original chart, press CTRL+Z to use the zoom out function.

![](data:image/png;base64,)
